text: Kabiné Komara (born 8 March 1950) is the Prime ministers of Guinea from 2008 to 2010.Guinée: un banquier nommé premier ministre He graduated from HEC Paris, University of Colorado Boulder, American University in Cairo and Rennes School of Business.La junte nomme un banquier au poste de Premier ministre He has been replaced by Jean-Marie Doré.Passation de pouvoir entre Kabiné Komara et Jean-Marie Doré == References == Category:1950 births Category:Living people Category:Alumni of HEC Paris Category:Prime ministers of Guinea
